Any pointers ?  I have had a set a while now but haven't had the time or desire  to get to it yet.

@tycivicsi make sure you set aside a good portion of your day. Bring the wheels and tires in the house if you can(much easier to do it in the A/C). Get a can of acetone and a bunch of cleaning rags and clean the tires really well(I mean really well). Clean the backs of the stickers as well. Follow the YouTube videos and do everything they say. And cover the entire sticker with the glue. The ends and point of the letters are the most important. And lastly make sure you allow the glue time to dry. The videos say minimum 1 hour. I let mine cure for at least 12.
Be generous with the glue but don't go crazy. Make sure you have enough for all 4 tires
